<b><font color=purple>Wynn~ and Wyn are two different people. One male and one female. Easily confusable we know. It's okay.</font><br><br>
<b>When two individuals clash, their stats are taken into consideration. The system of statistics was added for a reason.<br><br>
<b>When two jutsu clash, several things must be taken into consideration: Opposing and Defending Elements, Skill Ranks, Jutsu Ranks, and Pertinent Perks.<br><br>
<b>When a Genjutsu is being used, in order to check the results: Opposing Intelligence as well as pertinent mind perks and the Genjutsu and Genjutsu Resistance Stats.<br><br>
<b>The descriptions of perks is not a coverall in some cases. While your perk may state, "The user can break bones with an unguarded strike." This does not neccessarily mean that every unguarded strike will break a bone, nor does it mean that a guarded strike will spare any bones broken.<br><br>
<b>Descriptions are fluid as is combat. For this reason, Perk descriptions will be taken wholly into consideration unless an admin must be called to regulate a combat situation, in this case, perk descriptions will be majorly ignored and stat differences will be taken more into consideration.<br><br>
<b>Fuuinjutsu perks work in two different and distinct ways. One, in order to use high level Fuuinjutsu techniques, one must first have a corresponding perk, and Two, if you have a Fuuinjutsu perk that gives you the ability to say, "Seal off a certain amount of chakra from an individual." If there is no technique that does that specific thing, you are free to do it via the perk and not a jutsu.<br><br>
<b>Common Knowledge is just that: Common knowledge. If something is said to be common knowledge then everyone knows.<br><br>
<b>Because of the ways that clans work. You have IC knowledge of every member of your respective clan. You may not have intimate knowledge of them, but you will at the very least recognize them and know their name.<br><br>
